currency has collapsed, and its debt is junk. Next up is a potential defaul=
t that could cost investors billions and shut the country out of most fundi=
ng markets.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Warning lights are flashing as =
the government kickstarts the process of paying $117 million in interest on=
 dollar bonds Wednesday, a key moment for debt holders who=E2=80=99ve alrea=
dy seen the value of their investments plunge since Russia invaded Ukraine =
last month.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The government says that =
all debt will be serviced, though it will happen in rubles as long as sanct=
ions =E2=80=94 imposed because of the war =E2=80=94 don=E2=80=99t allow dol=
lar settlements. Failure to pay, or paying in local currency instead of dol=
lars, would start the clock ticking on a potential wave of defaults on abou=
t $150 billion in foreign-currency debt owed by both the government and Rus=
sian companies including Gazprom, Lukoil and Sberbank. =E2=80=A6</p><p styl=
e=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Signs of looming financial damage are becoming appare=
nt at many of the world's biggest money managers, including BlackRock Inc. =
and Pacific Investment Management Co. But it=E2=80=99s not likely to be lim=
ited to these giant funds. Because much of Russia=E2=80=99s debt was rated =
investment grade just weeks ago, the securities were pervasive across globa=
l fixed-income portfolios and benchmarks, meaning the impact could ripple a=
cross pension funds, endowments and foundations.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16p=
x 0;">=E2=80=9CThis will be a monumental default,=E2=80=9D said Jonathan Pr=
in, a portfolio manager at Greylock Capital Associates. =E2=80=9CIn dollar =
terms, it will be the most impactful emerging-market default since Argentin=
a=E2=80=99s. In terms of broader market impact, it=E2=80=99s probably the m=
ost broadly felt emerging-market default since Russia itself in 1998.=E2=80=
=9D</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yeah, I don=E2=80=99t know=
, I mean. If Russia doesn=E2=80=99t pay interest tomorrow, or pays it in ru=
